<item>
            <title>[SOLR-704] improve NumberFormatTransformers handling of invalid input</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-704</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As described in &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/java/library/j-numberformat/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/java/library/j-numberformat/&lt;/a&gt; instances of the NumberFormat class don&apos;t throw ParseExceptions in all cases of invalid input. This affects the org.apache.solr.handler.dataimport.NumberFormatTransformer class which relies on NumberFormat. I will attach a patch to demonstrate and fix this issue shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
